Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125} onto a piece of #foil{} with half the @unsalted butter{30}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Boil a full #kettle{}, then pour the @boiling water{450} into a #measuring jug{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat (if you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal #saucepan{} and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} later).

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175} to the pan. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in the boiled water from your measuring jug and the @vegetable stock paste{20}, stirring well to combine. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid onto the pan (or cover with foil).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a small #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @pine nuts{15} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch the pine nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer to a small #bowl{}.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50}(crumbled). Roughly chop the @chives{1}(chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier).

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{25}, @fresh pesto{50}, half the chives and the remaining butter.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the pesto risotto between your #bowls{} and top with the roasted baby plum tomatoes, spooning over the juices from the parcel.

Scatter over the Greek style salad cheese and remaining chives, then finish with a sprinkling of toasted pine nuts. Enjoy!